@startuml security_flow_EN
!theme plain
title AuthGate — Security Detection & Alerting Flow

actor Client
participant "SecurityMiddleware\n(handler/middleware.go)" as MW
participant "RateTracker\n(security/ratelimit.go)" as Rate
participant "ScanRequest\n(security/monitor.go)" as Scan
database "13 Pattern Groups\n(~90 regexes)" as Patterns
participant "SecurityLogFunc\n(injected callback)" as LogFunc
participant "CloudWatch\n(aws/cloudwatch.go)" as CW
participant "CloudMonitor\n(aliyun/cloudmonitor.go)" as CM
participant "SNS / PagerDuty" as Alarm

== Every Request ==
Client -> MW : HTTP Request

== Layer 1: Rate Limiting ==
MW -> Rate : Record(IP, Path)
Rate -> Rate : sliding window 60s\nper-second buckets

note over Rate
  5 thresholds:
  ├─ RATE_ELEVATED_IP_PATH (LOW)     ≥10 req/60s same IP→same path
  ├─ RATE_BURST_PATH (MEDIUM)        ≥1000 req/60s same path
  ├─ RATE_BURST_IP_PATH (HIGH)       ≥100 req/60s same IP→same path
  ├─ RATE_BURST_IP (HIGH)            ≥500 req/60s same IP
  └─ RATE_STORM (CRITICAL)           ≥5000 req/60s global
end note

Rate --> MW : rate matches (if any)

== Layer 2: Pattern Scanning ==
MW -> MW : io.ReadAll(r.Body) → buffer body
MW -> Scan : ScanRequest(body, path, query, headers)

Scan -> Patterns : scan 4 sources × 13 groups

note over Patterns
  CRITICAL (25 regexes):
  ├─ SQL_INJECTION  — UNION, DROP, OR '1'='1', SLEEP(), xp_cmdshell
  └─ COMMAND_INJECTION — ;cat, |ls, `id`, $(whoami), &&wget

  HIGH (46 regexes):
  ├─ XSS              — <script>, onerror=, javascript:, eval(), document.cookie
  ├─ PATH_TRAVERSAL   — ../../, /etc/passwd, /proc/self/
  ├─ SSRF             — 169.254.169.254, metadata.google.internal
  ├─ FILE_INCLUSION   — php://, /wp-admin/, .ini?%00
  ├─ NOSQL_INJECTION  — $gt, $where, $regex
  ├─ SENSITIVE_FILE   — .env, .git/, config.json, id_rsa, Dockerfile
  ├─ XML_ATTACK       — <!ENTITY ... SYSTEM, <![CDATA[

  MEDIUM (15 regexes):
  ├─ DIR_BRUTE_FORCE  — /admin, /wp-admin, /actuator/env, /jenkins
  ├─ CROSS_ORIGIN     — CSRF token patterns, cross-origin blocked
  └─ HEADER_INJECTION — \r\nLocation:, \r\nSet-Cookie:

  LOW (2 regexes):
  ├─ SCANNER_UA       — sqlmap, nikto, nessus, burp, zap, nmap
  └─ EXCESSIVE_PARAMS — &key=value patterns
end note

Scan --> MW : pattern matches (if any)

== Layer 3: Merge & Route ==
MW -> MW : all = rate matches + pattern matches

alt len(all) > 0
    MW -> LogFunc : SecurityLogFunc(method, path, srcIP, ua, all)

    group AWS Lambda
        LogFunc -> CW : LogSecurityEvent()
        note over CW
          Structured JSON → CloudWatch Logs:
          {
            "event": "security.threat",
            "severity": "CRITICAL",
            "category": "SQL_INJECTION",
            "match_count": 3,
            "path": "/auth/login",
            "source_ip": "1.2.3.4",
            "user_agent": "sqlmap/1.0",
            "matches": [...]
          }
        end note

        LogFunc -> CW : EmitSecurityMetric()
        note over CW
          EMF → CloudWatch Metric:
          Namespace: AuthGate/Security
          Metric: ThreatDetected (Count)
          Dimensions: Category, Severity
        end note
    end

    group Aliyun FC
        LogFunc -> CM : LogSecurityEvent()
        note over CM
          Structured JSON → SLS:
          same payload as CloudWatch
        end note
    end
end

== Layer 4: Alarm Chain ==
group CloudWatch Alarms
    CW -> CW : Metric Filter\n{ $.severity = "CRITICAL" }
    CW -> CW : Alarm: count >= 1 per 1 min
    CW -> Alarm : SNS → PagerDuty / Slack / Email
    note over Alarm
      CRITICAL → PagerDuty (page on-call)
      HIGH     → Slack #security-alerts
      SQL_INJECTION → Security team email
      RATE_STORM → PagerDuty + DingTalk
    end note
end

group CloudMonitor Alerts (SLS)
    CM -> CM : Alert Query\nseverity: CRITICAL | SELECT COUNT(*)
    CM -> CM : Trigger: cnt >= 1
    CM -> Alarm : 短信 / 电话 / 飞书 / 钉钉
end

== Request NEVER blocked ==
MW -> MW : next(w, r)
note over MW : detection-only\nblocking at WAF / API Gateway layer

@enduml
